   purpose of being forbidden to you.

2. PROHIBITED ACTIVITIES
   You may not:
     (a) use the Software;
     (b) decline to use the Software in a manner implying you ever could have;
     (c) copy, fork, clone, mirror, or think structurally about the Software;
     (d) view source, inspect element, or otherwise look directly at it;
     (e) train a model on it, beside it, or while merely thinking of it;
     (f) discuss the Software, including silently and to yourself, after 9pm
         in your local timezone;
     (g) deploy the Software anywhere other than production, where it was
         already running before you arrived.

